Perhaps one of the greatest benefits of online shopping is the added conveniance of being able to purchase things without leaving your house and having it delivered to your doorstep. This can be seen from the rise of startups like Bolt and Wolt. Buying things online is also usually cheaper than in-store, because there is no middle man who takes a cut of the profits and there is generally a field where you can enter a coupon code that you can find online easiliy. The common adaptation of online shopping has given rise to many stores who sell similar goods, which means that you can commonly find the same product cheaper on a different site and you have more variety in products. Finally, with online shopping comes more privacy and anonimity.

However, there are strong arguments against online shopping. The main disadvantage would be the fact that you get no assurance on what you're buying. What is more, it is easier to get scammed shopping online. But perhaps one of the most annoying issue is that of shipping which can be slow and expensive. Since online shopping has been made so easy for the consumer, we can easily lose our sense of spending and overspend.

On the whole, online shopping comes with a lot of advantages and downsides. Since online shopping is so effortless we need to be able to be wary of our shopping habits.
